TitleSelect: Health and Wellness: "20 Bộ câu hỏi & Trả lời | Exploring Health and Wellness: Insights and Perspectives"
ListenList: Are you a member of a health spa or gym?
Maria is a member of a local gym and goes regularly.
John prefers to exercise at home rather than join a gym.
Anna occasionally uses a health spa but doesn't have a membership.
Are you afraid of needles?
Maria is quite afraid of needles and avoids them whenever possible.
John is not afraid of needles and handles injections well.
Anna doesn't mind needles but doesn't enjoy them either.
Are you healthy?
Maria considers herself to be in good health and takes care of her body.
John feels he is moderately healthy but could improve his diet.
Anna thinks she is healthy because she exercises and eats well.
Are your parents healthy?
Maria's parents are generally healthy, although they have some minor issues.
John's parents have a few health problems but are managing them well.
Anna's parents are in excellent health and stay active.
Do you think that you need to lose weight?
Maria feels she is at a healthy weight and doesn't need to lose any.
John believes he could lose a few pounds to improve his fitness.
Anna is comfortable with her weight and focuses more on overall health.
Do you always eat healthy food?
Maria tries to eat healthy most of the time but occasionally indulges in treats.
John eats healthy during the week but allows himself some cheat meals on weekends.
Anna is very strict about her diet and rarely eats unhealthy food.
Do you bruise easily?
Maria bruises easily and often has marks from minor bumps.
John does not bruise easily and rarely notices any bruises.
Anna bruises occasionally but not very often.
Do you catch a cold more than once a year?
Maria usually gets a cold once or twice a year.
John rarely gets colds and considers himself to have a strong immune system.
Anna gets colds a few times a year, especially during winter.
Do you consider alcohol a drug?
Maria considers alcohol to be a drug because it affects the body and mind.
John thinks alcohol is different from other drugs but can be harmful if abused.
Anna agrees that alcohol is a drug and should be consumed responsibly.
Do you drink a lot?
Maria drinks socially but in moderation.
John drinks more on weekends but tries to limit his intake.
Anna rarely drinks alcohol and prefers non-alcoholic beverages.
Do you eat a lot of vegetables?
Maria eats a lot of vegetables and includes them in every meal.
John eats vegetables regularly but not in large quantities.
Anna follows a plant-based diet and consumes a lot of vegetables.
Do you eat lots of fruit?
Maria enjoys fruit and eats several servings a day.
John eats fruit occasionally but prefers vegetables.
Anna loves fruit and makes sure to include it in her daily diet.
Do you ever get headaches?
Maria gets headaches occasionally, especially when stressed.
John rarely gets headaches and doesn't consider them a problem.
Anna suffers from migraines and gets headaches frequently.
Do you exercise? What kind of exercise do you do? How often do you exercise?
Maria exercises regularly, focusing on cardio and yoga.
John goes jogging and lifts weights a few times a week.
Anna practices Pilates and goes to the gym for strength training.
Do you go for regular medical check-ups?
Maria goes for a medical check-up once a year.
John only goes to the doctor when he feels unwell.
Anna believes in preventive care and goes for regular check-ups.
Do you go to the dentist's twice a year?
Maria visits the dentist every six months for a check-up.
John tries to go to the dentist once a year but sometimes skips appointments.
Anna makes sure to go to the dentist twice a year without fail.
Do you have a lot of stress?
Maria experiences stress often due to work and personal responsibilities.
John manages his stress well and rarely feels overwhelmed.
Anna has some stress but practices mindfulness to keep it under control.
Do you normally go to one doctor in particular or any available doctor?
Maria prefers to see the same doctor for consistency and trust.
John goes to any available doctor when needed.
Anna always visits her family doctor for any health concerns.
Do you have any allergies?
Maria is allergic to pollen and some types of nuts.
John has no known allergies.
Anna is allergic to certain medications and shellfish.
Do you think pets are good for a person's health?
Maria believes pets can significantly improve a person's mental and physical health.
John thinks pets are beneficial but require a lot of responsibility.
Anna feels pets provide companionship and can help reduce stress.

Delving into various aspects of personal health and wellness.
Discussing the impact of healthy lifestyles on overall well-being.
Examining different perspectives on maintaining a healthy lifestyle.
